results.title: Daggett County Commission | Daggett County, UT - Official Website
results.description: Commission seats are filled through the partisan political system. All Daggett County positions are At-Large positions and represent the entire county. Commissioners are elected for a four year term; Commissioner Jack Lytle was elected in the 2018 election and re-elected in 2018. Commissioner Randy Asay was elected in 2016 and re-elected in 2020.

results.title: Free Fishing Day in Utah is quickly approaching — What ... - ABC4 Utah
results.description: There are several great Utah fishing destinations to check out this time of year, according to the Utah Division of Wildlife Resources. They say that right now, the fish are "hungry and biting.". Free Fishing Day will be celebrated on Saturday, June 8 — allowing anyone to fish at any public waterbody in the Beehive State without a license.
